data.title: Spring Days at Lake Tegel Shot with LomoChrome Purple 110 · Lomography
data.meta_description: The LomoChrome Purple 110 film, even with its pocket-sized format, continues to share big dreams of surreal violets especially with these springtime images by Lomographer bnjmn.

written by rocket_fries0036 on 2024-05-06 #gear #people #places

With the Diana Baby 110, Lomographer @elwynreverie uses the iconic and distinct characteristics of the camera and pocket film format to create dream-like images.

Rebirth of a Myth: Hélène Virion and the History of Petzval Lens

written by mpflawer on 2024-08-12 #gear #culture #news #people

Researcher and visual artist Hélène Virion has devoted years of her life to practical and theoretical research on photography. One of her notable studies is centered on the iconic Petzval lens. Explore the topic further and get a glimpse of her artistic world through this interview!

Lesley J's Apartment Cafe with the Lomo'Instant Square

written by eloffreno on 2024-08-12 #gear #culture #people

New York City-based analogue enthusiast Lesley J. has two passions — trying out new film cameras and making at-home coffee creations. Combining the two, she tried out the Lomo'Instant Square Glass camera to document her at-home cafe serving her friends and family.
